# Magic: The Gathering | Marvel Super Heroes Collecting Knowledge Base

Source article: Wizards of the Coast, "Collecting Magic: The Gathering | Marvel Super Heroes: The Four Most Important Things to Know", published June 2, 2026.

This file is a paraphrased, structured knowledge-base digest of the source page. It is not a verbatim copy of the article. Use it to answer questions about Magic: The Gathering | Marvel Super Heroes product contents, release timing, set codes, legality, Booster Fun treatments, booster collation, and prerelease contents.

---

## 1. Core Set Facts

- Product line: Magic: The Gathering | Marvel Super Heroes.
- Tabletop release date: June 26, 2026.
- MTG Arena release date: June 23, 2026.
- Prerelease event window: June 19–25, 2026.
- Main set code: MSH.
- Commander set code: MSC.
- Source Material Cards set code: MAR.
- The set combines Magic gameplay with characters, locations, artwork, and stories from the Marvel Universe.

### Legality

- MSH cards are legal in all Magic formats.
- MSC and MAR are Eternal-legal sets: legal in Commander, Legacy, and Vintage.
- Individual MSC/MAR cards may also be legal in other formats where those cards are already legal.
- Play Boosters can contain cards from both MSH and MAR.
- Cards opened from Play Boosters are playable in Magic: The Gathering | Marvel Super Heroes Draft and Sealed.

