## 4. Four Main Collecting Highlights

### 4.1 The Mind Stone

The Mind Stone is a major collectible card in the set and appears in three versions:

1. Main set version.
   - Artwork by Volkan Baga.
   - Available in non-foil and traditional foil.
   - Found in both Play Boosters and Collector Boosters.

2. Borderless Gauntlet version.
   - Shows the stone with Thanos imagery.
   - Traditional foil only.
   - Found only in Collector Boosters.

3. Textless cosmic foil version.
   - Ultra-limited Marvel collectible.
   - Fewer than 150 copies printed.
   - Found only in Collector Boosters of any language.
   - Always English.

### 4.2 Borderless Classic Comic Cards

- Borderless classic comic cards use historic Marvel comic artwork on new-to-Magic legendary creature cards.
- These cards are positioned as premium collectibles and potential Commander centerpiece cards.
- There are 15 mythic rare classic comic cards.
- 4 of the classic comic cards are double-faced cards.
- They are traditional foil only.
- They are found only in Collector Boosters.
- They can appear in Collector Boosters of any language, but the cards themselves are always English.

### 4.3 Borderless Source Material Cards

- Borderless source material cards combine Marvel comic artwork with Magic reprints.
- Featured Marvel artists include names such as Jack Kirby, Alex Ross, Dan Adkins, and Tony S. Daniel.
- This category includes source material versions of legendary creatures from Secret Lair’s Marvel Superdrop.
- There are 60 source material cards.
- Three of the 60 are different versions of Heroic Intervention.
- Source material cards have equal appearance rates within the source material card pool.
- A non-foil source material card replaces a common in roughly 1 in 24 Play Boosters.
- Every Collector Booster contains one non-foil or traditional foil source material card.

### 4.4 Borderless Logo Cards

- Borderless logo cards use stylized Marvel character art on monocolor backgrounds with character logos.
- They appear on legendary creatures from across the set.
- There are 15 rare logo cards and 13 mythic rare logo cards.
- They appear in non-foil and traditional foil versions.
- They can be found in Play Boosters and Collector Boosters.

